        <hl1>Golf Humbles All</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>John Birdsall letter contends that no one masters golf, even Tiger Woods (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I love the game of golf, and I admire the athleticism of Tiger Woods.</p>
        <p>But no man is the master of golf.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>I love the game of golf, and I admire the athleticism of Tiger Woods.</p>
        <p>But no man is the master of golf.</p>
        <p>It is a maddening aspect of the game that just when you think you're in control, the game rises up to choke your hubris. How many of us have shot a 40 on the front followed by a 50 on the way in?</p>
        <p>Tiger is just another one of us poor souls. He'll probably miss the cut at the British Open.</p>
        <p>JOHN BIRDSALL  New York</p>
      </block>
